definition: to sell/to reach (a price in an auction)
to sell/to betray/to spare no effort/to show off or flaunt

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
variant of 出[chu1] (classifier for plays or chapters of classical novels)

sentences.english: And the Gunners will fund it with their windfall for ex-skipper Patrick…
sentences.chinese: 枪手将会用卖出前队长的前来收购他。

sentences.english: Boeing ( BA - news - people ) can sell more planes than Airbus.
sentences.chinese: 波音公司可以比空中客车卖出更多的飞机。

sentences.english: I shall sell my house by auction.
sentences.chinese: 那楝房子在拍卖时以很低价卖出。

sentences.english: Middle rate is the arithmetic average rate of buying rate and selling rate, used for inter-bank.
sentences.chinese: 中间汇率是买入汇率和卖出汇率的算术平均数。

sentences.english: Eventually some people realize this and start to sell out.
sentences.chinese: 最终，一些人会意识到这一点，并开始卖出。

sentences.english: No one knows what happened to the legions of unsold copies of her book.
sentences.chinese: 谁也不知道，她那一大批没卖出的书上哪儿去了。

sentences.english: Robey left New York without having made a sale, and stopped in Philadelphia on the way home.
sentences.chinese: 罗比没有卖出邮票离开纽约，回家的路上他停脚费城。

sentences.english: Bayern Munich team manager Uli Hoeness has revealed the club are set to sell a number of their players in January.
sentences.chinese: 拜仁经理霍胖已透露将在明年一月卖出对内一些球员。

sentences.english: He has a profit on everything he sells.
sentences.chinese: 他卖出每样东西都获利。

sentences.english: Today, Amazon sells more e-books than paperbacks.
sentences.chinese: 今天，亚马逊卖出的电子书比纸质书可要多。

sentences.english: Do you plan to sell it or opensource it as a standalone application?
sentences.chinese: 你们有把它作为一个独立应用卖出去或开源的计划吗？

sentences.english: These Bonds were sold at a premium.
By the time Haggis began reading it, “Dianetics” had sold about two and a half million copies.
sentences.chinese: 当哈吉斯拜读此书时，它已经卖出了250万本。

sentences.english: An instruction to a broker to buy or sell shares, stocks, commodities, currencies, etc; , as specified, at the best possible price.
sentences.chinese: 要求以当时可能的最优价位成交的买入或卖出指令。

sentences.english: Oh, now the asking price is $90 each share.
sentences.chinese: 哦，现在卖出价每股90美元。
人们总会买进卖出，一直如此。

definition: to take an inventory of stock/to clear out one's stock
to sell/to betray/to spare no effort/to show off or flaunt
to take money or valuables out of storage/to recover/to ship goods/to extract (chemicals from solution)
to sell off/to get rid of in a sale
to dump (selling abroad more cheaply than cost price at home)
